Straco Grup SRL, a Romanian
construction company, won a 17.7 million-lei ($5.3 million)
contract for water network upgrades in the south of the country
from regional utility  Apa Service SA .  The utility received 12 bids for the contract, initially
estimated at 23 million lei, which includes water infrastructure
upgrade works in the town of Bolintin Vale, according to a May
